1
00:00:24,375 --> 00:00:26,875
[tires screech]

2
00:00:31,125 --> 00:00:33,666
A good little girl
would have been in bed by now.

3
00:00:33,750 --> 00:00:35,666
A good girl wouldn't beat you!

4
00:00:35,750 --> 00:00:37,916
You've got some spunk.

5
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,458
[BOTH grunt]

6
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:43,541
[shouting]

7
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:17,083
[shouting]

8
00:02:20,083 --> 00:02:23,166
Your form is stiff. You leave
too many openings that way.

9
00:02:23,250 --> 00:02:24,625
You should try to relax a bit.

10
00:02:24,708 --> 00:02:27,000
[grunts, shouts]

11
00:02:28,208 --> 00:02:29,333
[grunts]

12
00:02:38,583 --> 00:02:41,958
I know you're
probably stronger than me...

13
00:02:42,041 --> 00:02:44,625
but I still have to find
a way to defeat you.

14
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:47,875
I'm doing this for everybody!

15
00:02:47,958 --> 00:02:50,708
But especially for my mom,
'cause she deserves better!

16
00:02:52,250 --> 00:02:53,916
[OSSIE grunts]

17
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:55,666
--[MOMO] Get her!
--[CHI barks]

18
00:02:57,166 --> 00:02:58,166
[MOMO] Ossie!

19
00:03:00,541 --> 00:03:02,083
[squawks]

20
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:06,750
--[URA] Hey!
--Mr. Slo!

21
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:09,083
[shouts]

22
00:03:09,166 --> 00:03:10,791
[yelps]

23
00:03:10,875 --> 00:03:13,375
[grunting]

24
00:03:17,208 --> 00:03:18,541
[MR. SLO grunts]

25
00:03:18,625 --> 00:03:20,500
Give this up and go home.

26
00:03:20,583 --> 00:03:23,166
Your life may be poor,
but it's peaceful.

27
00:03:23,250 --> 00:03:24,833
[footsteps approach]

28
00:03:26,208 --> 00:03:27,416
[gasps]

29
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:30,333
Mom?

30
00:03:30,416 --> 00:03:33,375
Time to go home, Momo.
I didn't teach you to wield

31
00:03:33,458 --> 00:03:36,208
a sword so you could engage
in this sort of foolishness.

32
00:03:36,291 --> 00:03:37,541
[gasps]

33
00:03:40,708 --> 00:03:42,708
Don't try to stop me, Mom.

34
00:03:42,791 --> 00:03:45,500
I'm going to defeat her
if it kills me--

35
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:53,916
Momo! Hey, is she all right?
Why did you knock her out?

36
00:03:55,916 --> 00:03:57,125
You see her?

37
00:03:58,333 --> 00:04:00,125
That's Momo's real mother.

38
00:04:00,208 --> 00:04:01,625
[BOTH gasp]

39
00:04:01,708 --> 00:04:03,958
[HARU] She's too young
to understand.

40
00:04:04,041 --> 00:04:05,208
I couldn't tell her.

41
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:09,625
[sighs]

42
00:04:10,916 --> 00:04:13,375
No. That's not it.

43
00:04:16,958 --> 00:04:19,250
I just wanted more time.

44
00:04:19,333 --> 00:04:21,583
A little longer
to be her mother.

45
00:04:23,666 --> 00:04:27,000
[URA] If it isn't master fencer
Haru Fujiwara. It's been while.

46
00:04:27,083 --> 00:04:30,541
This troublemaker is
your daughter, then?

47
00:04:30,625 --> 00:04:33,083
What can I say, Ura?
She takes after her mother.

48
00:04:33,166 --> 00:04:34,791
[URA]
It seems so.

49
00:04:36,666 --> 00:04:39,250
[VILLAGERS gasp]

50
00:04:39,333 --> 00:04:41,708
Stay calm, everyone.
These dolls may look scary,

51
00:04:41,791 --> 00:04:44,666
but they can't hurt you.
I can assure you of that.

52
00:04:44,750 --> 00:04:47,333
They may appear threatening,
but they're harmless.

53
00:04:47,416 --> 00:04:49,541
--[VILLAGERS gasp]
--Is that really true?

54
00:04:49,625 --> 00:04:50,708
[MAN]
They sure look dangerous.

55
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:52,625
[HARU]
The state vigilante squad,

56
00:04:52,708 --> 00:04:55,291
the Okayama Demons,
does not exist anymore.

57
00:04:55,375 --> 00:04:58,500
The only one living
in this demon castle is you.

58
00:04:59,958 --> 00:05:01,958
You were the Best
who protected Okayama,

59
00:05:02,041 --> 00:05:04,333
defending it
from Hiroshima's attacks,

60
00:05:04,416 --> 00:05:06,083
keeping it safe
from those pirates

61
00:05:06,166 --> 00:05:07,666
without honor or humanity.

62
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:09,416
Until you turned your back.

63
00:05:11,375 --> 00:05:15,416
I demand to know the reasons
for thy betrayal, Ura Kukino!

64
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:19,666
[laughs] You always were
old-fashioned, weren't you?

65
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:21,291
All right then,

66
00:05:21,375 --> 00:05:23,500
let's see if I can put this into
words that you'll understand.

67
00:05:24,916 --> 00:05:27,750
Don't waste thy breath,
'tis a lost cause!

68
00:05:28,791 --> 00:05:30,875
[grunts]

69
00:05:36,125 --> 00:05:37,125
[motorcycle approaches]

70
00:05:39,208 --> 00:05:40,375
[gasps]

71
00:05:44,625 --> 00:05:48,250
[NOZOMI running]
Um. Hold on! Kaguya!

72
00:05:50,583 --> 00:05:51,666
Uh...

73
00:05:56,833 --> 00:05:58,291
Sorry, but there's
a visitor here

74
00:05:58,375 --> 00:06:00,791
from Okayama...
looking for Fuhito.

75
00:06:00,875 --> 00:06:04,208
He wants Kuramochi?
Then he can go to the hospital.

76
00:06:04,291 --> 00:06:07,291
It sounds like it's really
important, though!

77
00:06:10,083 --> 00:06:12,833
--[sighs]
--[NOZOMI] What's your plan?

78
00:06:12,916 --> 00:06:15,000
Going to get back at them?

79
00:06:15,083 --> 00:06:16,875
--[grunts]
--Oh!

80
00:06:17,916 --> 00:06:19,625
I won't let you do that!

81
00:06:21,458 --> 00:06:24,833
You're not even a real
peacebroker, so why try so hard?

82
00:06:24,916 --> 00:06:26,458
[NOZOMI]
I don't like it!

83
00:06:26,541 --> 00:06:29,750
Sounds silly, huh?
But that's how I feel.

84
00:06:29,833 --> 00:06:32,333
I get that I'm nobody.

85
00:06:32,416 --> 00:06:35,208
Not a Best.
Just a lame stand-in.

86
00:06:36,250 --> 00:06:38,583
A stupid, meddling outsider.

87
00:06:38,666 --> 00:06:40,750
But I can't just do nothing!

88
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:42,250
[gasps]

89
00:06:47,541 --> 00:06:50,500
[MAN] I am the former captain
of the Okayama Demons.

90
00:06:50,583 --> 00:06:52,000
My name is Kibino.

91
00:06:54,583 --> 00:06:57,500
[KAGUYA] An agreement between
Hiroshima and Okayama?

92
00:06:57,583 --> 00:07:00,250
[KIBINO] Ura Kukino wanted
to protect the country

93
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:03,583
even if it meant becoming
an enemy of all its citizens.

94
00:07:03,666 --> 00:07:06,750
So she made a secret pact
with Hiroshima, got rid

95
00:07:06,833 --> 00:07:09,083
of all the squad members,
and became a demon.

96
00:07:09,166 --> 00:07:12,375
But that charade will not
be useful much longer.

97
00:07:12,458 --> 00:07:15,125
If Kuramochi makes
everything known to the public--

98
00:07:15,208 --> 00:07:17,750
not for retribution,
but for justice--

99
00:07:17,833 --> 00:07:19,125
he could save everybody

100
00:07:19,208 --> 00:07:22,291
from the depredations
of the Ishizukuri Stones.

101
00:07:22,375 --> 00:07:24,333
[KAGUYA]
Shima Ishizukuri is

102
00:07:24,416 --> 00:07:26,583
from a former
branch family line.

103
00:07:26,666 --> 00:07:29,125
If Okayama acknowledges
the secret agreement,

104
00:07:29,208 --> 00:07:32,000
then the former head family
will bring about justice.

105
00:07:32,083 --> 00:07:36,166
[KIBINO] Yes. However, the
captain does not agree with me.

106
00:07:36,250 --> 00:07:38,625
And since the citizens
have begun an uprising,

107
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:40,916
I thought I would come here
to explain the situation

108
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,041
and convince Kuramochi
to lend us his help.

109
00:07:44,125 --> 00:07:46,083
[KAGUYA]
I guess I shouldn't be surprised

110
00:07:46,166 --> 00:07:48,041
he never said
anything about this to me.

111
00:07:48,125 --> 00:07:50,250
[chuckles]
He's always like that,

112
00:07:50,333 --> 00:07:54,041
carrying everything
on those broad shoulders of his.

113
00:07:54,125 --> 00:07:55,875
Doesn't he know
he's not the only one

114
00:07:55,958 --> 00:07:57,458
who can serve this family?

115
00:08:00,541 --> 00:08:02,791
--Let's get going.
--[gasps]

116
00:08:02,875 --> 00:08:05,416
[chuckles]
Justice awaits.

117
00:08:08,375 --> 00:08:10,291
[BOTH grunt]

118
00:08:10,375 --> 00:08:12,708
Okay, wait.
That walking cupcake over there

119
00:08:12,791 --> 00:08:15,291
is actually Momo's mom?
That's nuts!

120
00:08:17,208 --> 00:08:20,125
There's a reason the president
was always so busy.

121
00:08:20,208 --> 00:08:21,500
She's been working hard
for years,

122
00:08:21,583 --> 00:08:23,291
trying to return you
to your home planet,

123
00:08:23,375 --> 00:08:25,166
to get you back
to your real family.

124
00:08:25,250 --> 00:08:29,375
Real family. What about Mom?
What's that make her?

125
00:08:29,458 --> 00:08:30,250
[grunts]

126
00:08:31,666 --> 00:08:34,541
Well, she's your mom, too.
She always will be.

127
00:08:35,958 --> 00:08:38,041
He was right.

128
00:08:38,125 --> 00:08:39,458
[BOTH grunt]

129
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:47,958
The way I see it,
they're both her moms, right?

130
00:08:48,041 --> 00:08:51,666
Uh... they're both--
yeah, you're right!

131
00:08:52,708 --> 00:08:54,666
Let me borrow this a sec, Momo.

132
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:57,875
[grunts] Okay!

133
00:08:57,958 --> 00:08:59,666
--[shouting]
--[VILLAGERS gasp]

134
00:08:59,750 --> 00:09:01,916
--[MAN] What're you doing?
--[WOMAN] You're gonna get hurt!

135
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:04,208
[grunting]

136
00:09:07,583 --> 00:09:08,916
Hey, what's happening?

137
00:09:10,375 --> 00:09:12,083
[screams]

138
00:09:12,166 --> 00:09:15,208
--That's gotta hurt!
--What was she trying to do?

139
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:19,875
[AI] Haru!

140
00:09:19,958 --> 00:09:21,375
Don't, Ai! Stay back!

141
00:09:21,458 --> 00:09:24,083
[grunts] If you don't want
Momo to fight her,

142
00:09:24,166 --> 00:09:25,625
you gotta lead by example!

143
00:09:25,708 --> 00:09:28,125
You have to back down
and stop fighting her, too!

144
00:09:28,208 --> 00:09:30,000
I don't know the whole story,

145
00:09:30,083 --> 00:09:32,000
but you're both her moms,
aren't you?

146
00:09:32,083 --> 00:09:33,500
[gasps]

147
00:09:44,208 --> 00:09:48,000
[grunts] Aw, man!
What's up with this thing?

148
00:09:48,083 --> 00:09:50,250
I thought the stone
would make me a Best,

149
00:09:50,333 --> 00:09:53,375
but it's not helping me at all.
I still have to stop them!

150
00:09:53,458 --> 00:09:55,125
--U-tan, no!
--Come back!

151
00:09:55,208 --> 00:09:56,500
[WOMAN]
Really? Again?

152
00:09:56,583 --> 00:09:59,458
[BOTH grunting]

153
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,500
[URA thinks]
Is she really?

154
00:10:07,541 --> 00:10:11,083
You abandoned her!
How could you ever do that?

155
00:10:11,166 --> 00:10:15,125
What was so important
that you could even consider it?

156
00:10:15,208 --> 00:10:18,083
I said not to waste
your breath! Didn't I?

157
00:10:19,166 --> 00:10:22,708
--[screams]
--Are we too late?

158
00:10:22,791 --> 00:10:25,750
--Nonsuke is here!
--Why's Chi here?

159
00:10:25,833 --> 00:10:28,583
Nonsuke! U-tan is in trouble!

160
00:10:28,666 --> 00:10:30,166
--Huh?
--[grunts]

161
00:10:30,250 --> 00:10:31,458
[NOZOMI] Ai?

162
00:10:33,416 --> 00:10:35,416
[grunts]

163
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:40,833
[NOZOMI]

164
00:10:42,083 --> 00:10:44,500
Whoa! What's happening?

165
00:10:45,625 --> 00:10:47,291
[grunting]

166
00:10:50,458 --> 00:10:51,583
Huh?

167
00:10:52,708 --> 00:10:55,041
[ANIMALS whimpering]

168
00:11:05,458 --> 00:11:08,833
[BOTH shouting]

169
00:11:20,041 --> 00:11:23,541
--[ALL groan]
--Huh?

170
00:11:30,125 --> 00:11:33,208
[CHI whimpering]

171
00:11:33,291 --> 00:11:34,958
A dog! [yelps]

172
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:38,541
Hold on!
Stop fighting, okay?

173
00:11:38,625 --> 00:11:39,958
There's something
you need to hear!

174
00:11:40,041 --> 00:11:42,625
Uh... Nozomi?

175
00:11:52,291 --> 00:11:54,583
[URA] I'm too stubborn
for my own good.

176
00:11:54,666 --> 00:11:56,750
I never did learn
when to back down.

177
00:11:56,833 --> 00:11:58,833
[KIBINO]
Of course you couldn't.

178
00:11:58,916 --> 00:12:00,625
Only someone with great resolve

179
00:12:00,708 --> 00:12:02,250
could have become
a demon as you did.

180
00:12:02,333 --> 00:12:05,166
And through it all you stayed
by my side, didn't you?

181
00:12:05,250 --> 00:12:08,000
[KIBINO] Of course I did.
It was all I could do.

182
00:12:09,166 --> 00:12:10,708
Please. Tell me her name.

183
00:12:10,791 --> 00:12:12,166
It's Momo.

184
00:12:14,958 --> 00:12:18,541
[URA] Thank you.
You raised her to be strong.

185
00:12:18,625 --> 00:12:20,750
[HARU]
Well, she does have your genes.

186
00:12:20,833 --> 00:12:23,458
[URA] That may be true,
but she also has your spirit.

187
00:12:23,541 --> 00:12:25,916
[MOMO groans] Huh?

188
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:29,041
She goes after what she wants,
no matter what anyone says.

189
00:12:35,625 --> 00:12:38,250
[sighs]

190
00:12:38,333 --> 00:12:41,291
And people like that only become
stronger, the more they learn.

191
00:12:41,375 --> 00:12:43,500
[winces] Huh?

192
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:54,125
Well, I think
that's all you need me for.

193
00:12:54,208 --> 00:12:56,375
Is there anything else
I can do to help?

194
00:12:56,458 --> 00:12:57,791
Yeah, me too.

195
00:12:57,875 --> 00:13:00,041
I want to do what I can
to help the people of Okayama.

196
00:13:00,125 --> 00:13:03,208
Ura Kukino has given me
her word of honor.

197
00:13:03,291 --> 00:13:06,125
Now there's an upstart
branch family to deal with,

198
00:13:06,208 --> 00:13:08,083
and that's going to be my job.

199
00:13:09,375 --> 00:13:10,833
Thank you.

200
00:13:11,875 --> 00:13:13,000
[giggles]

201
00:13:14,916 --> 00:13:16,791
[truck departs]

202
00:13:22,750 --> 00:13:24,041
Uhh...

203
00:13:24,125 --> 00:13:26,750
Uhh... [laughing]

204
00:13:26,833 --> 00:13:28,166
Hey, what're you laughing at?

205
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:30,416
At your face.
You look really terrible!

206
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:33,458
Huh! You don't look
so good yourself.

207
00:13:33,541 --> 00:13:36,083
[laughs]

208
00:13:36,166 --> 00:13:40,291
So, uh, I'm sorry.

209
00:13:40,375 --> 00:13:43,083
I'm really sorry, too.
Glad you're back.

210
00:13:43,166 --> 00:13:45,333
[NOZOMI and AI laughing]

211
00:13:47,250 --> 00:13:49,166
Hey, Nonsuke. Where's Yukippe?

212
00:13:49,250 --> 00:13:50,833
--Huh?
--Ah!

213
00:13:56,416 --> 00:13:59,375
I have to get that stone back
for Shigyo as soon as possible!

214
00:13:59,458 --> 00:14:01,208
She can't return
to normal without it.

215
00:14:01,291 --> 00:14:03,833
I don't know whether
or not she can be a Best again,

216
00:14:03,916 --> 00:14:05,625
but she could
at least leave the hospital.

217
00:14:05,708 --> 00:14:07,208
Without the stone,
all I can do

218
00:14:07,291 --> 00:14:09,250
is stay by her side
and comfort her.

219
00:14:09,333 --> 00:14:11,208
But I can't even do
that much for her

220
00:14:11,291 --> 00:14:13,000
when I'm stuck
inside this stupid cell!

221
00:14:13,083 --> 00:14:15,500
Stupid, stupid,
stupid, stupid cell!

222
00:14:15,583 --> 00:14:17,750
[chuckles]

223
00:14:17,833 --> 00:14:22,166
♪ Nameless stones,
we're all rolling along ♪

224
00:14:22,250 --> 00:14:24,833
♪ Through the seasons
of the sun ♪

225
00:14:24,916 --> 00:14:27,791
♪ When the world
kicks you around ♪

226
00:14:27,875 --> 00:14:29,958
♪ Throws you to the ground... ♪

227
00:14:30,041 --> 00:14:31,666
Hey, that's Momi-Ham
you're singing.

228
00:14:31,750 --> 00:14:33,500
That song always
helps me feel better,

229
00:14:33,583 --> 00:14:35,250
like I can make
a difference in the world,

230
00:14:35,333 --> 00:14:37,041
even though
I'm just one little person.

231
00:14:37,125 --> 00:14:38,500
I know how you feel.

232
00:14:38,583 --> 00:14:41,166
My friends and I sing it
together all the time, too.

233
00:14:41,250 --> 00:14:42,375
--[MOMIYAMA] "Stones," huh?
--[gasps]

234
00:14:42,458 --> 00:14:44,125
I can't believe
girls as young as you

235
00:14:44,208 --> 00:14:45,291
would know a band that old.

236
00:14:45,375 --> 00:14:47,750
Well, my parents
introduced them to me.

237
00:14:47,833 --> 00:14:50,666
Yeah, there were a lot of kids
who listened to them growing up.

238
00:14:50,750 --> 00:14:54,166
That long, huh? Hard to believe
so much time has passed.

239
00:14:55,458 --> 00:14:57,041
[gasps] Oh my gosh!

240
00:14:57,125 --> 00:14:59,708
You're Momizo from
Momiyake Hammers, aren't you?

241
00:14:59,791 --> 00:15:00,750
No!

242
00:15:02,791 --> 00:15:07,000
"Kuranosuke Momiyama." Momizo.

243
00:15:07,083 --> 00:15:08,375
[MOMIYAMA] Sorry, kid, not me.

244
00:15:12,250 --> 00:15:14,500
--Think you can guide us out?
--[YUKINA] Huh?

245
00:15:14,583 --> 00:15:16,583
You got here yourself.
You weren't dragged in,

246
00:15:16,666 --> 00:15:19,333
so you know best where we are.
Think you can do it?

247
00:15:19,416 --> 00:15:21,958
[gulps]
Yeah, sure!

248
00:15:25,625 --> 00:15:28,375
[OTOMO] There's something about
this relic of the evil Takumis.

249
00:15:28,458 --> 00:15:30,250
I know we agreed not to expose

250
00:15:30,333 --> 00:15:32,041
that it was
in our possession, but--

251
00:15:32,125 --> 00:15:35,250
Why? What is it? Did you
remember something from before?

252
00:15:35,333 --> 00:15:38,250
What? Oh, no.

253
00:15:38,333 --> 00:15:41,125
I have no memories from before
I woke up here that day.

254
00:15:41,208 --> 00:15:42,458
It's all a blank.

255
00:15:42,541 --> 00:15:45,083
[SHIMA]
I see. It's fine, then.

256
00:15:45,166 --> 00:15:46,208
[grunts]

257
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:49,916
--[SHIMA] What's wrong?
--It's nothing.

258
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:51,083
[FATCHO on P.A.]
Pardon, ma'am.

259
00:15:51,166 --> 00:15:53,166
There are messengers
from Tokorozawa.

260
00:15:54,958 --> 00:15:56,666
[MASAMI]
Whoa! What is all this?

261
00:15:56,750 --> 00:15:58,041
[SHIGYO]
Maybe they're trying to start

262
00:15:58,125 --> 00:16:00,041
an archipelago conquest project.

263
00:16:00,125 --> 00:16:01,291
[MASAMI] Huh?

264
00:16:01,375 --> 00:16:02,500
[SHIGYO]
There are groups out there

265
00:16:02,583 --> 00:16:04,166
who've started doing
exactly that,

266
00:16:04,250 --> 00:16:06,458
like a reaction against
what the world's become

267
00:16:06,541 --> 00:16:09,333
--in recent years.
--Seriously?

268
00:16:09,416 --> 00:16:11,541
Things seem to be
snowballing out of control.

269
00:16:11,625 --> 00:16:13,625
I think there's more going on
than anybody knows.

270
00:16:13,708 --> 00:16:15,375
[SHIMA] As I'd expect
of the woman called

271
00:16:15,458 --> 00:16:17,750
the Trigger
of the Great Tokyo War.

272
00:16:17,833 --> 00:16:19,375
You're very perceptive.

273
00:16:19,458 --> 00:16:20,708
I certainly hope that's

274
00:16:20,791 --> 00:16:22,833
a real octopus pot engine unit
you've got.

275
00:16:22,916 --> 00:16:24,541
It's not like
we had a lot of time

276
00:16:24,625 --> 00:16:26,375
on our hands
to whip up a fake one.

277
00:16:26,458 --> 00:16:29,083
First return the hostage,
then you can have it.

278
00:16:29,166 --> 00:16:31,083
[SHIMA]
Unfortunately, she's gone.

279
00:16:31,166 --> 00:16:33,916
--[BOTH] Huh?
--I know, what a drag, huh?

280
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:35,125
I'll be taking that unit now.

281
00:16:35,208 --> 00:16:37,500
[grunts]
We had a deal!

282
00:16:37,583 --> 00:16:40,416
You don't think
we can put up a fight?

283
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:43,583
If you want the octopus pot,
return Otonashi now!

284
00:16:43,666 --> 00:16:46,791
Don't forget. We have
to push the button first.

285
00:16:46,875 --> 00:16:48,166
Huh? Oh, yeah.

286
00:16:48,250 --> 00:16:49,916
[grunts]

287
00:16:51,250 --> 00:16:52,541
Crap! Shigyo!

288
00:16:52,625 --> 00:16:54,750
--[GUYS laugh]
--These chicks are pathetic.

289
00:16:54,833 --> 00:16:56,625
--Let's get them!
--[GUYS shouting]

290
00:16:56,708 --> 00:16:58,583
--Charge her!
--Knock her out!

291
00:16:59,833 --> 00:17:01,416
[GUY]
Think they're really that weak?

292
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:03,666
[GUY 2] Nah!
I think we're just that strong!

293
00:17:03,750 --> 00:17:04,916
[GUY]
Yeah, that's right!

294
00:17:06,125 --> 00:17:08,125
[BOTH moan]

295
00:17:08,208 --> 00:17:12,041
Good, now mount it
onto the Stonefish.

296
00:17:12,125 --> 00:17:14,250
Well, what are you waiting for?
Hurry up.

297
00:17:21,125 --> 00:17:24,083
With this, we can expand
Okonomiyaki Village

298
00:17:24,166 --> 00:17:25,500
to the surface of the moon.

299
00:17:25,583 --> 00:17:27,708
I guess you wanted to go,
too, didn't you?

300
00:17:27,791 --> 00:17:29,208
--Huh?
--Oh, come on.

301
00:17:29,291 --> 00:17:30,833
I see how you stare up at night.

302
00:17:30,916 --> 00:17:32,583
I didn't realize.

303
00:17:32,666 --> 00:17:33,708
--[explosion]
--[BOTH gasp]

304
00:17:38,416 --> 00:17:40,208
Shima Ishizukuri.

305
00:17:40,291 --> 00:17:43,083
I'm here as a descendant
of the Nayotake family.

306
00:17:43,166 --> 00:17:45,208
You're guilty
of severe misconduct.

307
00:17:45,291 --> 00:17:46,958
I've come to make you pay.

308
00:17:47,041 --> 00:17:49,000
Kaguya Nayotake.

309
00:17:49,083 --> 00:17:52,333
Have you come to avenge
old Kuramochi?

310
00:17:54,750 --> 00:17:56,541
I've come to punish you!

311
00:17:58,750 --> 00:18:00,708
[NOZOMI] Where do you think
Yukina could have gone?

312
00:18:00,791 --> 00:18:03,000
I don't know.
Maybe she went back to the shop.

313
00:18:03,083 --> 00:18:06,041
I doubt it. I don't think
there'd be any reason to.

314
00:18:06,125 --> 00:18:08,416
[AI] Hey, can we talk
about that stone?

315
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:10,291
--Yeah! Let's stop a sec.
--[grunts]

316
00:18:10,375 --> 00:18:12,583
--[AI] Well?
--[NOZOMI] My stone.

317
00:18:12,666 --> 00:18:14,208
I've had it with me
this whole time,

318
00:18:14,291 --> 00:18:16,500
but I never came close
to being a Best.

319
00:18:16,583 --> 00:18:18,625
Yeah. I think
that's pretty obvious.

320
00:18:18,708 --> 00:18:20,708
--Uhh...
--Here's the thing.

321
00:18:20,791 --> 00:18:24,833
Those stones are--
oh, is that Yukippe?

322
00:18:24,916 --> 00:18:26,625
[NOZOMI and AI] Huh?

323
00:18:26,708 --> 00:18:28,833
[NOZOMI gasps]
It's Kuramochi!

324
00:18:31,125 --> 00:18:32,916
Hey. I'm really
starting to think

325
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:34,458
that you have
no sense of direction.

326
00:18:34,541 --> 00:18:37,541
You're wrong. That's not it.
I'm fine with directions.

327
00:18:37,625 --> 00:18:40,583
Okay, so you're absolutely sure
this is the way you came?

328
00:18:40,666 --> 00:18:43,458
Uh, maybe we should take
a quick break.

329
00:18:43,541 --> 00:18:45,000
Maybe you should answer
the question!

330
00:18:45,083 --> 00:18:47,541
--[clangs]
--[engine powering up]

331
00:18:50,250 --> 00:18:53,125
[GUYS scream]

332
00:18:53,208 --> 00:18:56,166
As the Nayotake successor,
it is my duty to see

333
00:18:56,250 --> 00:18:57,708
that you pay
for your wrongdoing.

334
00:18:57,791 --> 00:19:00,833
You backed Okayama's Best
into a corner.

335
00:19:00,916 --> 00:19:02,583
You made people suffer!

336
00:19:02,666 --> 00:19:05,375
Apologize and return
the money you exploited.

337
00:19:05,458 --> 00:19:08,166
Finally,
relinquish the squad license

338
00:19:08,250 --> 00:19:09,833
to which you have no right.

339
00:19:11,375 --> 00:19:12,916
No, I don't think so.

340
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:17,500
Hiroshima used to be united.
Do you remember that?

341
00:19:17,583 --> 00:19:19,666
The main family,
the branch families,

342
00:19:19,750 --> 00:19:21,208
and the respectable folks--

343
00:19:21,291 --> 00:19:25,416
everyone rough around the edges,
but all of 'em good people.

344
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:27,958
You were one of them!
Or have you forgotten?

345
00:19:28,041 --> 00:19:30,083
What are you talking about?

346
00:19:30,166 --> 00:19:32,625
I may've been young,
but I remember.

347
00:19:32,708 --> 00:19:35,958
You played with me!
You weren't always pirate scum.

348
00:19:36,041 --> 00:19:38,458
[laughs]
Sounds like a nice memory.

349
00:19:38,541 --> 00:19:40,416
Would you like to know
what I remember?

350
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:42,291
Because I'm happy to tell you.

351
00:19:42,375 --> 00:19:44,083
I remember how all those people

352
00:19:44,166 --> 00:19:46,541
who looked after
the Nayotake family treated us

353
00:19:46,625 --> 00:19:48,791
once it was ruined
by the family war.

354
00:19:48,875 --> 00:19:51,458
They all pretended
not to know us.

355
00:19:51,541 --> 00:19:52,958
[shouts]
Do you remember that?

356
00:19:57,416 --> 00:20:00,500
Is that some kinda excuse
for what you're planning?

357
00:20:00,583 --> 00:20:02,333
Whatever it is, I'll stop you.

358
00:20:02,416 --> 00:20:05,375
[SHIMA] Think long and hard
before you try anything.

359
00:20:05,458 --> 00:20:07,666
You really believe
you can defeat me?

360
00:20:07,750 --> 00:20:11,125
You don't stand a chance.
Want to know what I'm planning?

361
00:20:11,208 --> 00:20:14,750
I'll tell you. I'm gonna make
this whole archipelago

362
00:20:14,833 --> 00:20:18,000
without honor and humanity
part of Okonomiyaki Village!

363
00:20:20,041 --> 00:20:21,416
[gasps]

364
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:23,500
[powering up]

365
00:20:23,583 --> 00:20:25,500
[groans]

366
00:20:29,666 --> 00:20:31,250
[grunts]

367
00:20:37,500 --> 00:20:38,458
[KAGUYA grunts]

368
00:20:39,958 --> 00:20:43,250
"The only people who matter
are ourselves and our own.

369
00:20:43,333 --> 00:20:46,458
Everybody else is
just part of the Rest."

370
00:20:47,541 --> 00:20:48,875
That's how most people think.

371
00:20:51,708 --> 00:20:53,041
But not everyone.

372
00:20:53,125 --> 00:20:55,958
There are still people
out there who want to help,

373
00:20:56,041 --> 00:20:58,750
who ask nothing in return
but a stupid stone.

374
00:20:58,833 --> 00:21:00,000
[gasps]

375
00:21:00,083 --> 00:21:01,708
[KAGUYA] Who haven't
given up on the world!

376
00:21:01,791 --> 00:21:04,166
Sounds to me
like those people are idiots.

377
00:21:06,291 --> 00:21:08,541
Stop! What are you doing?

378
00:21:08,625 --> 00:21:11,541
I have no use
for moldy scraps of paper.

379
00:21:11,625 --> 00:21:14,083
What I really wanted was this.

380
00:21:15,166 --> 00:21:16,416
[KAGUYA gasps]

381
00:21:18,333 --> 00:21:20,083
[chuckles]
How sad,

382
00:21:20,166 --> 00:21:22,708
for a descendant
of the main family not to know.

383
00:21:26,125 --> 00:21:29,875
During the Great Tokyo War,
there was a robot with abilities

384
00:21:29,958 --> 00:21:33,250
that surpassed those of both
the Tokyo Tower Robot

385
00:21:33,333 --> 00:21:35,708
and the Tokyo Skytree Robot.

386
00:21:35,791 --> 00:21:39,750
The chivalrous robot, Daimon!

387
00:21:39,833 --> 00:21:41,041
[breathes shakily]

388
00:21:43,875 --> 00:21:46,291
There they go.
I believe they're all finished.

389
00:21:46,375 --> 00:21:50,041
Hey, wake up! It looks like
the ship has been completed,

390
00:21:50,125 --> 00:21:52,125
so half of this has gone
according to plan.

391
00:21:52,208 --> 00:21:53,458
Huh?

392
00:21:53,541 --> 00:21:55,333
Once we have control of it,
we'll get Otonashi.

393
00:21:55,416 --> 00:21:58,666
And next time, be sure
to press the button, okay?

394
00:21:58,750 --> 00:22:00,083
[clicks]

395
00:22:00,166 --> 00:22:02,666
--[sproings]
--[BOTH gasp]

396
00:22:02,750 --> 00:22:04,875
[SHIMA]
Excellent work, men.

397
00:22:04,958 --> 00:22:08,583
Next, why don't I have you
mass produce this robot?

398
00:22:08,666 --> 00:22:12,083
I am still in possession
of the sacred Takumi object

399
00:22:12,166 --> 00:22:14,625
that you brought out
during the turmoil.

400
00:22:14,708 --> 00:22:17,000
I'm assuming
that you would like it back.

401
00:22:20,916 --> 00:22:23,375
--Now. Move!
--[MEN shouting]

402
00:22:23,458 --> 00:22:25,375
[gasps]

403
00:22:25,458 --> 00:22:30,458
It's the end of Hiroshima's
false chivalry! Say good bye!

404
00:22:32,583 --> 00:22:34,791
--It's a chivalrous...
--Robot...

405
00:22:34,875 --> 00:22:36,500
Called Daimon?

406
00:22:36,583 --> 00:22:39,125
It was made
when Hiroshima was in crisis

407
00:22:39,208 --> 00:22:40,583
and is intended to be ridden

408
00:22:40,666 --> 00:22:43,000
by successors
to the Nayotake name.

409
00:22:43,083 --> 00:22:45,708
I heard that, during
the family war, it was stolen

410
00:22:45,791 --> 00:22:48,791
from the storehouse
by the Abe branch family,

411
00:22:48,875 --> 00:22:52,375
and then taken by the Isonokami
before finally ending up

412
00:22:52,458 --> 00:22:55,125
in the hands
of the pirate Shima Ishizukuri.

413
00:22:55,208 --> 00:22:58,458
But it won't run on its own.
It needs another component.

414
00:22:58,541 --> 00:23:02,083
That's probably why she wanted
the squad license so badly.

415
00:23:02,166 --> 00:23:04,250
--[GIRLS] Huh?
--Thanks to me,

416
00:23:04,333 --> 00:23:06,458
Kaguya's rushed
into this situation blindly.

417
00:23:06,541 --> 00:23:08,500
You said your name was Nozomi?

418
00:23:08,583 --> 00:23:10,083
[NOZOMI]
Yes. That's right.

419
00:23:10,166 --> 00:23:13,250
Please help us.
Bring this to Kaguya Nayotake.

420
00:23:13,333 --> 00:23:15,166
So much depends
on her right now.

421
00:23:17,375 --> 00:23:19,333
[GIRLS gasp]

422
00:23:19,416 --> 00:23:20,791
[CHIAYA] Takoyaki?

